      • getNextNode

        public Node getNextNode(int id)
        Returns the Node with min ID greater than input. Returns null if no next exists. Provided id does not need to exist in the tree.
        Parameters:
        id - key for which a Node with next higher key will be found. Does not need to exist in the Tree.
        Returns:
        Node with min ID greater than input

      • getPreviousNode

        public Node getPreviousNode(int id)
        Returns the Node with max ID lesser than input. Returns null if no next exists. Provided id does not need to exist in the tree.
        Parameters:
        id - key for which a Node with next lower key will be found. Does not need to exist in the Tree
        Returns:
        Node with max ID lesser than input

      • delete

        public boolean delete(int id)
        Deletes Node with key == id and rebalances. Does nothing if key does not exist in Tree.
        Parameters:
        id - key of Node to be deleted
        Returns:
        delete success

      • increase

        public int increase(int theID,
                    int m)
        Increases the value at the node with provided key. If the node does not exist, it will be inserted with value m.
        Parameters:
        theID - key of the node to increase
        m - amount by which that node's value should be increased
        Returns:
        resulting node value

      • decrease

        public int decrease(int theID,
                    int m)
        Decreases the value at the node with provided key. If the value goes below 0, the node will be deleted. Returns 0 if the node does not exist or is deleted.
        Parameters:
        theID - key of the node to decrease
        m - amount by which that node's value should be decreased
        Returns:
        resulting node value. Will return 0 if deleted
